To Ed and our Silent Friend:<br><br>
My anger is born out of experience with Doc Spatz since the beginning of this site. Have no concern, because my anger has nothing whatwever to do with your path in this matter. You have your own way in handling things, and I respect that, and it will not interfere in our future discourse.<br><br>
My contempt for Doc Spatz is very interesting because it has grown over time. How many times must I conquer my contempt? The effort grows with each encounter. The law of diminishing returns is at hand, and Doc's venom grows with each event. It is as if these things are meals upon which to gorge, then digest, then start all over again, in a habitual, manipulative, and expansive manner.<br><br>
Finding this situation completely unacceptable is a natural evolution of my thought, and has nothing to do with falling prey to my emotions.<br><br>
    *I do not desire to have my emotions serve as prey.* <br><br>
There is a distinct difference in these two things. <br><br>
Emotions are things to be shared, regardless of their orientation, intensity, or state of agreement. They are to be respected. They are not a fault, but an asset. <br><br>
Ed and Cook, neither of you did *anything* to deserve the objectionable vomit to which we have of late been all subjected. I have hit the high water mark. The water has been steadily rising over time as others stumbled into this lair and were subjected to the same treatment. Althgough some of the words change, the same context and meaning are always there.<br><br>
Here is a little something from last winter, a blast from the past!<br>
---------------------------------------<br>
**** DR. SPATZ<br>
